3. cs.LG (Machine Learning): Although not directly related to machine learning, the paper's focus on parsing and recognizing patterns in language may be relevant to the sub-category of machine learning that deals with natural language processing. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper establishes lower bounds for the time complexity of parsing tree-adjoining grammars, which is a problem in computational complexity theory. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper involves analyzing the structure of tree-adjoining grammars and their parsing algorithms, which may involve concepts from discrete mathematics.
